This paper deals with data cleaning and query answering in the context of matching dependencies, which are a type of data dependencies commonly used in database systems. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on data cleaning and query answering, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category.
